All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
AbstractTaskList
Class for abstract lists of tasks; contains name of task list and number of completed tasks
ActiveTaskList
Class for list of Active Tasks called "Active Tasks"; extends AbstractTaskList for construction
ISortedList<E extends Comparable<E>>
Interface for a list that keeps objects in sorted order as defined by the Comparable interface.
ISwapList<E>
Interface for a list that changes the position of elements through swap operations.
Notebook
Notebook class; Contains an ISortedList of TaskLists, one ActiveTaskList, an AbstractTaskList for the currentTaskList, a notebookName, and boolean flag that keeps track of if the Notebook has been changed since the last save.
NotebookReader
Class for reading Notebooks from file
NotebookWriter
NotebookWriter class; in charge of writing notebooks to given files
SortedList<E extends Comparable<E>>
Class for a list that keeps objects in sorted order as defined by the Comparable interface.
SwapList<E>
Class for a list that changes the position of elements through swap operations.
Task
Task class; contains the information about each individual task including the taskName, taskDescription, if the task is recurring, and if the task is active.
TaskList
Class for list of tasks; extends AbstractTaskList and implements Comparable interface
WolfTasksGUI
Container for the WolfTasks project that provides the user the ability to interact with notebooks, task lists, and tasks.
